1	 Preference Toward Risk  - Risk Averse /  Neu­
tral /  Seeking (Loving) 

Three  diﬀerent  kinds  of  behaviors: 

Risk Averse (Figure 1) 
•  Facing  two payoﬀs with  the same expected  value, prefer the less risky  one. 
•  Diminishing  marginal  utility  of  income. 
•	 Relation  between  the  utility  of  expected  value  and  expected  utility 
u(E (x)) > E (u(x)). 

Example. 

u(x) = ln x. 

Risk Neutral (Figure 2) 
•  Facing  two  payoﬀs  with  the  same  expected  value,  feel  indiﬀerent. 
•  Linear  marginal  utility  of  income. 
•	 Relation  between  the  utility  of  expected  value  and  expected  utility 
u(E (x)) =  E (u(x)). 

