Table  2:  Diversiﬁcation:  Selling  Air  Conditioners  and  Heaters. 

•	 If  one  only  sells  air  conditioners  or  heaters, 
E (prof it) = 21,  000, 

σ(prof it) = 9,  000. 

•	 If  the  company  puts  half  of  its  eﬀorts  in  selling  air  conditioners  and 
half  of  its  eﬀorts  in  selling  heaters,  then  the  proﬁt  is  always  21,000 
no  matter  the  weather  is  cold  or  hot. 

E (prof it) = 21,  000, 

σ(prof it) = 0. 

Thus  we  should  choose  to  sell  both  to  reduce  risk.


